Task:

Attach Public IP to Azure Virtual Machine

The Nautilus DevOps team has already set up a virtual machine and allocated a public IP address. The final task is to attach this public IP to the VM's network interface card (NIC).

An existing VM named devops-vm-pip and a public IP address named devops-pip already exist.

Attach the public IP devops-pip to the network interface of the VM devops-vm-pip.

Make sure the VM is properly assigned the public IP.


Solution:

Search for the existing VM, nic and the public IP addresses and view them.
Stop the running VM as we are updating the nic.
Go the the existing VM-->Networking-->Network settings.
Click configure from the public IP address.
View the existing primary type IP configuration.
Click add and enable associate public IP address.
Enter the name as devops-pip.
Choose the devops-pip from the dropdown of public IP address.
Network interface will get updated.
Start the VM.
